        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14144",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "concerning these few lines from the front controller:\n\n-----------------------------------------------------\n                 \/**\n                  * Dispatch request\n                  *\/\n                 $dispatcher->dispatch($request, $response);\n\n                 \/**\n                  * Notify plugins of dispatch completion\n                  *\/\n                 $this->_plugins->postDispatch($request);\n             } while (!$request->isDispatched());\n         } catch (Exception $e) {\n             if ($this->throwExceptions()) {\n                 throw $e;\n             }\n-----------------------------------------------------\n\nit appears as though if an exception is thrown from the action\ncontroller, plugins are not notified of postDispatch().  Is this the\nintended behavior?\n\nAside from that, would be the best method for catching the following errors:\nNon-Existent Controller\nNon-Existent Action\nException Due to User Application Code\n\nI've seen a few different attempts at a solution over the course of the\ndifferent iterations of ZF Controllers, but still curious what people think? ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-04-11T16:24:31.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-04-11T16:24:31.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14156",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Once we get the action helpers into core, we will have Zend_Controller_Action_Exception present again. This will allow catching using the following:\n\n* Zend_Controller_Dispatcher_Exception => invalid controller\n* Zend_Controller_Action_Exception => typically invalid action method, but possibly helper exception\n* Exception => other application exception\n\nI am in the process of modifying and testing the functionality as requested.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-04-12T12:25:02.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-04-12T12:25:02.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14157",
                    "author": {
